<article class="announcement">

  <section class="summary">
    <p>A day to bring together the designers and developers of the future of the web.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="details">
    <p>
      On <em>Wednesday 9th April</em>, back-to-back with JSConf AU, the historic <a href="http://www.thatsmelbourne.com.au/Placestogo/TheatreVenues/AllTheatreVenues/Pages/7467.aspx">Melbourne Arts House</a> will be filled with international and local experts, tasty food, great coffee, and plenty to talk about.
    </p>
    <div class="photo">
      <div class="image"><img src="images/meat-market.jpg" alt="Melbourne Arts House, 1874"></div>
      <p>Melbourne Arts House, 1874</p>
    </div>
    <p>
      It will be a special one-track, one-day conference following on from the fantastic <a href="http://cssconf.com/">CSSConf US</a> and <a href="http://2013.cssconf.eu/">CSSConf EU</a> events. There’ll also be some fun activities around the conference day, allowing you to see parts of wonderful Melbourne and hang out with some new friends.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="subscribe">
    <p class="limited"><strong>Tickets go on sale early 2014 and will be strictly limited.</strong></p>
    <p>Ticket availability will be announced via our mailing list and the <a href="https://twitter.com/cssconfau">@cssconfau</a> Twitter account. Sign up below to ensure you don’t miss out:</p>
